7:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Binance calculates funding rates every 8 hours using the premium index and interest rate differential, applying payments at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. Hyperliquid updates funding rates hourly based on the 1-minute TWAP of the premium, allowing for more frequent arbitrage opportunities and faster capital efficiency. Both exchanges use similar premium calculations, but Hyperliquid's hourly frequency means rates adjust more quickly to market conditions. The shorter interval on Hyperliquid reduces the risk of large funding payments but requires more active position management."}]]}]
8:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which exchange offers better funding rate arbitrage opportunities?","answer":"Hyperliquid's 1-hour funding intervals create 8x more arbitrage opportunities per day compared to Binance's 8-hour cycle. However, Binance's deeper liquidity allows for larger position sizes with minimal slippage."},{"question":"How do the funding rate calculation methods differ?","answer":"Both use premium-based calculations, but Hyperliquid updates hourly using 1-minute TWAP while Binance updates every 8 hours. This makes Hyperliquid more responsive to short-term market movements."},{"question":"Which platform is better for institutional arbitrage?","answer":"Binance suits institutional traders needing deep liquidity and established custody solutions. Hyperliquid appeals to institutions wanting on-chain transparency and faster capital velocity."},{"question":"What are the key operational differences for arbitrageurs?","answer":"Binance requires KYC and has withdrawal limits, while Hyperliquid operates without KYC but only supports USDC. Hyperliquid's on-chain nature provides verifiable settlement but limits cross-chain arbitrage strategies."}]}]
